      "content": "Right, I see. If we're looking at the \"cultural factors\" or \"inherent predispositions\" argument you mentioned—to make the paper balanced, I need to understand the logic there. Are there specific datasets or schools of thought that attempt to quantify how much of these crime disparities are attributed to those biological or cultural factors versus the systemic ones? Basically, I'm looking for the \"pro-disparity\" side of the academic debate to ensure I'm not just presenting one perspective.",
